storyInfo: Skadi effortlessly sorts out the inhabitants hostile to her, and meets a girl named Anita who's willing to communicate. Anita gives her directions, and assists her in searching for Specter. At the same time, another set of eyes has been watching Skadi all along.

attributes.text: Skadi watches as the locals fall unconscious, and she picks up the suitcase she'd laid for a second on the floor.

attributes.content: ...Gr—Greetings.
Hm? There's another one.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Don't—Don't hit me... I'm not very much like them. I know you're good.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: You can understand what I mean.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You only came here following Bench.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: *Whimper*... Woodframe, Woodframe...
attributes.name: Young Inhabitant

attributes.content: He ran, I followed.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You bear no ill will towards us.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: All I ask is he gives what's mine back.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: B—Bench... what did you take?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: All shiny... all shiny... hard... it hurts... *whimper*...
attributes.name: Young Inhabitant

attributes.content: That's not for you to eat! Pull it out of your mouth, quick!
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: I'm sorry, Bench tends to just grab at things he's never seen before. He doesn't understand these are things he shouldn't grab.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: (Receives necklace)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Ugh, it's covered in spit... It's gotten your hand dirty.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: It's fine, as long as I have it back.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: We don't often see unfamiliar faces here. Did you come from the outside?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: I came from a city elsewhere in Iberia.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: It's very rare I see people from other places.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Your clothes... are very strange too. I've never seen material like this before. Does everyone from the outside dress that way?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Only wandering singers would.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Wandering... singers? I overheard you talking to Sheetmetal, but I don't know what that is.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Like me, they travel everywhere, occasionally stopping over, playing the harp, singing a song.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: What about the case? What's inside it?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: A saxophone.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: What's a saxophone?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: An instrument.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Are you really a wandering singer?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Mm.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: (Quiet mutter)
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: So what did you come to do, then? Was it sing?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: I came to find someone.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Who? Also a wandering singer?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Yes. She is a fellow of mine. We are colleagues.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Did she come to Sal Viento too?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Correct. Have you seen her?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You haven't told me what she looks like yet... oh, well! I said it just before, but you're the first time I've ever seen anyone like you.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: I'll go and ask others. Can you guide me?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Guide? That trap... was my making. I thought you would've known.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: I don't care.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You don't fault me? I thought you would at least have... reproached me some.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Let's go. I'm in a hurry.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Alright...
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Agh!
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Why—Why did you suddenly stop...? I knocked against your case. Ow...
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: I forgot to say. What's in my case is useless to you.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Apart from this, anything you might want, I can give you once you help me find her.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Er, I was only curious... Was I that apparent?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: As plain to see as the trap you made.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Wow... singer, you not only have a pair of nimble hands, but a pair of formidable eyes too.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Ninety-eight...
attributes.name: Inhabitant

attributes.content: Ninety-nine...
attributes.name: Inhabitant

attributes.content: How do I ask questions here?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Huh? How do you usually ask them on the outside?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: (With a thump, she sets down the case she was carrying.)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: With this.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Um? The saxo... saxophone? You use instruments to ask questions?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Slam slam, boom, kapow.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: The sounds this instrument makes are quite bizarre.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: It's very effective. They all usually open up straight away.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: If they still don't talk, I can change angle, and go for another round.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Then I have a feeling that won't get you anywhere here.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Possibly.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: (Strokes case)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: In that case, the two just now. They already got talking.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Sheetmetal? They shouldn't even know of musical instruments. The people here usually keep themselves to themselves, and don't pay attention to anyone.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: And they, er, talk very infrequently. Even if they knew, they wouldn't understand how to reply.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: You've paid attention to me.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Probably because I'm a little odd. I'm not too like everyone else.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: You talk a lot better than they do too.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Do I really? I'm so happy. It's all what Grandma Petra taught me.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Oh, if you want to find someone else to ask, I can bring you to Grandma Petra. She's the oldest one of us all here, and knows about the most too.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Alright.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Come, singer, let us walk through here.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Here?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Ninety-nine, ninety-nine...
attributes.name: Inhabitant

attributes.content: Ninety-nine.
attributes.name: Inhabitant

attributes.content: Do you mean them? You can ignore them, they're just standing around. They make it a bit of a squeeze, but it'll be alright even if you bump into them. They won't react, really. Will you, Tableleg?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Wha? She jumped—clear over their heads? H—How did she manage that? She didn't so much as touch anyone beneath her.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Do all people from the outside walk about like this? How magical!
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Made it!
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Grandma Petra! Graaaandmaaaa Petraaaa!
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Don't shout! Are you trying to shake my ears apart?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Hee-hee, grandma, you're so very lively today! You're still—er, are you basking in the sun?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: The sun... keh, where do you see the sun? I've been waiting all these years and I still haven't seen the sun. Anita, what are you getting up to? You're always scrambling about, doing this and that.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Around here, could anything important even happen?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Grandma Petra, I'm fine as I am. Someone else wanted to find you.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: —Huh, where'd she go?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.text: Skadi stares fixed at the alley's other end.
There's no one to be seen there. At least, it seems so.

attributes.content: How did you get over here all of a sudden?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Someone's watching.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: That so? Where? I can't see anyone around.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: They're hiding very well. Not well enough, is all.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Why are you so grim? Aren't you a wandering singer? Shouldn't you be very used to people staring if you perform?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: ...You're right.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Then let's make our way over! Grandma Petra's in alright spirits. You might really be able to ask something or other.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.text: At a street corner, an old lady rounds a pillar, turning circle after circle.
Her body trembles and shakes, yet her gait is no hobble.

attributes.content: Red sky at night, set aglow by my fiery clothes... beloved one, o, take me to fly o'er the deep blue ocean...
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Grandma Petra, what are you doing now?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Anita, oh, curse you, Anita! Did you not see I was dancing?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: When a young girl is dancing, nobody can disturb her. Are you going to dance along with me, Anita?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: I... I don't know how.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Spin a little slower. Watch you don't make yourself dizzy again.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Nonsense! How would I go dizzy? I could round it ten and some times, and the whole city would clap for me!
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: I... *cough* *cough* *cough*...
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Take a little break. Look, we have a wandering singer here. She has a question to ask you.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: A wandering singer? I've never seen any wandering singer in my good long years.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: This sunlight... this sunlight's carried on far too long. Why hasn't night come yet? Once the sun's turned in, there'll be people playing away in the bar... Will you be playing in there too?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: We dance in the square, yes, right here we do... oh, I could spin more times than you could count. I have a red skirt, girlie, and I must say, it's much more beautiful than the one you're wearing.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: So many youngsters want to dance with me. I like Manuel the most out of all of them. He was the most handsome when he was young.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Yes, Grandma Petra, you've told me this. You've told me plenty of times now.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Besides, who's looking for me?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Is it you? Your red dress is so pretty.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Red... no, I don't want... I don't want one red.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: The seawater! The seawater is alive!
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Oh, no, here it goes again...
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: ...suddenly came washing up. Everyone dead! All so fine... so many fine people. The survivors had nothing either to eat.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Manuel... Manuel told me he'd take me with him. Then he went back on that. He said all those people who left had never come back. All of them had died on the outside.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: You've told me this before as well.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: And then he said he'd protect me. He promised me—he said he'd protect me! But he only wanted to make a fool of me—
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: He wanted to swindle me out of all the food I'd kept—*cough* *cough*, I pretended to agree, and I took the silver vase my mother left behind—*cough* *cough* *cough* *cough*—
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Red... I like red... no, I don't want...
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Grandma Petra, Grandma Petra! Just leave it, okay? You always get out of breath once you start going on about this.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: The one I brought to see you today wanted to ask about something else.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Ask? Who's asking?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Her. A wandering singer from the outside.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Tell her who you're looking for, quickly! While Grandma Petra still has the strength to answer.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Hello—
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Who're you?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: A wandering singer. I'm searching for someone just like me, come from the outside as well.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: An out—An outsider! You're pulling my leg!
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: No outsider would ever come around these parts, they stopped caring about us long ago...
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: You came to steal something, didn't you? You're going to steal my food, my clothes, you're going to sup on my flesh, drink my blood—
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Monster! You're a monster!
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: (Frowns)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Grandma, there isn't a monster. She's just a wandering singer.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Red hem... red... I've found one, here... the singing has arisen... Manuel is waiting for me, I must go, I should go...
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Beloved one, o, set aglow by my fiery clothes... fiery clothes...
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: *Sigh*.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: I'm sorry, Grandma Petra's particularly worked up today. Maybe I shouldn't have brought you to see her.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: I'll take her back inside, singer. Give me a moment.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Singer, are you still looking for the one watching you?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.text: Across the opposite corner, a dark shadow stows away in an even deeper cloud's gloom.

attributes.content: I'm fine.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Lurking trouble is like a beastling too scared to bare its fangs. No need to care.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Grandma Petra was...
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: She knows of playing instruments, and knows to dance. The way she spoke was akin to an outsider.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Really? No wonder. She speaks of so much, I can't make heads or tails of it.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: She called me a monster.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: She didn't mean to. Grandma often sees things that aren't real. It's like she's dreaming all the time.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Who isn't.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: She's taken ill. She can't answer your question now.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: A shame.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Don't be worried.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: There are other brothers of mine where I live. I can take you to ask them in a while. I'm just not sure if they'll be willing to open up. Sometimes it really is so hard to speak with them.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Brothers?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Yes, brothers. You're an Iberian too. Don't you call them so?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: My mother had no other children—but—I have very many brothers and sisters. In this town, we are all brothers and sisters. That's what the laws say.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: And you believe in those.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: What else would we do? When I was very young, Grandma Petra even told me that in those dark days past, we had made mistakes.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: In those times, each one of us only looked after ourselves, hiding in each home, never speaking. Sometimes a can would be dug out, and we would, um, fight over it.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Then things gradually got better. Now we'll live together, and occasionally talk. Everyone's started to, erm—learn to share.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: —'We want to survive, so we must love one another even more. For love is the inseparable bond between us. We may not steal, we may not fight.'
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: 'Make oneself sturdy, but our whole self sturdier still. Only this way will bring a better life.'
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: This sounds familiar.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Really? The priest says everyone from the outside believes this too.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: I forgot to say, the priest taught us this!
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: He'll tell us so much every time... most of it is lost on me. Apart from those few words just now, all I remember is we need to treat each other as brothers, and be a little kinder to each other. I suppose it is nice advice, isn't it?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Priest?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Yes. Just like you, he came from the outside too. Though that was very many years ago.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: It was ever since he came that things improved. He's a brother among us.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Is he alone?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Most of the time he's alone. Oh, I heard from Sheetmetal's friends there was one more too, later on.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Who?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I've never seen her. She doesn't seem to show herself. Occasionally when the priest is speaking to us, she'll be standing behind him. I only ever see that one glimpse of her from far away.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Alright.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Why are you... in such a hurry suddenly? Do you need to go somewhere?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: I'm going to the chapel.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Do you know how to get there?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Your chapel isn't that hard to recognize.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: The way there's not so easy. You need to follow the coast from here. Come, let me show you.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.text: The girl leads Skadi along a lengthy stretch of path.
The two gradually near the shore, the chapel roof always somehow in their sight, yet still far away as ever.

attributes.content: Why did you stop?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: So they followed.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: What do you mean? You've lost me again.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: That clingy beastling.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: That's strange. You keep saying beastling—that should be an animal, right? We've got no animals living here—they disappeared long ago!
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: It's fine. Let's keep going.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Very well, friend from the outside. You're in charge.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: What did you see? It's right there.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: But we don't usually go to the chapel at this time.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: I have ways in.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You can enter, we all can. The chapel's entrance is forever open to the devout—the priest said so. But... you wanted to seek someone out, didn't you?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: He isn't usually in the chapel at this time.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: What times is he in?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Every so often, he'll appear before us of his own accord, and make friendly conversation with every one of us.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: If you have any issues, those are also times you can go find him. No matter what it is that bothers you, he'll never reject you.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: On such days, until the sun rises the next morning, he'll be in the chapel waiting.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: That's right, he can also help you in your search! I'm sure the priest would know much more than any of us!
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: How long is 'every so often?'
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Um, I haven't seen him in the recent while. I'm not like them—I don't really count the days. But it should be the next two days? All our food is about to run bare.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Alright.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Strange. Whenever you say alright, I always feel like it isn't a sincere reply.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: No, that's wrong of me. The priest said, we shouldn't doubt others. Ugh, they all say I'm so fond of thinking of all these questions, and it won't help me lead a good life in any way.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Were those also his words?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Haha, he'd never tell me this. I'd slip off before he knew it.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: It's Sheetmetal and his lot, they all hate me making a racket. And it's not like I'm always itching to say so much. The people here are all too quiet.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Whenever they won't talk, I get so bored, and the only thing I can do is talk to myself for hours on end.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: It used to be that only Grandma Petra would talk with me. And now you too, thank goodness. Oh, no. Do you think I'm annoying as well?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Where I come from, there are many who love speaking more than you do.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: It sounds like a wonderful place!
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: ...It's okay enough.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Where you come from, do the people dance? Just like Grandma Petra was mentioning, dancing in the square?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Occasionally.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Then why haven't I seen you dancing? I've noticed your harp.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Grandma Petra's told me. Don't you all dance around while you sing?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: My dance... none of you may see.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Why?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: The time, the place, and those before me are all not right.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You're so strange, practically stranger than me. Just where is your home? Are all the people where you're from as strange as you?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: (Plucks strings)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Where I'm from, there is no home.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: And I do not know where my home is. My home is long gone.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Well, that's okay. My home was long gone as well, years ago in a gale, when the building collapsed. My mamá was inside when it happened, and she's gone too.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: But that's okay. Everyone's in the same boat. If your house is gone, find another empty one and move in. Plenty of buildings fit the bill here.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: That's right, if you're not happy dancing, then can you sing for me?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: I've never heard anyone else sing before.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Maybe.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Wonderful!
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Oh, visiting so many places has gotten me hungry.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: You're hungry too, aren't you? If you're hungry, you can't sing, right?
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Let's go find something to eat.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Um...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Am I running too fast? I forgot you wouldn't know the way.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant

attributes.content: Right, I'm Anita! You can just shout my name from now on, and that way you won't be left behind. Call for me, and I'll stop and wait for you.
attributes.name: Female Inhabitant
